Note:
Evidence-of-correctness probe for the v0.0.8.5 modular ANNOTATION parser and
MACRO-expansion AST graph algorithms (task #494). Compile-pass is not
correctness; this drives the real reconciled surfaces on representative input
and asserts the observable behavior.

  Annotation parsing  -> AnnotationParser.parse_annotation_block over a real
                         Token stream (built with the lexical token constructor
                         and the canonical TokenStream/Parser wiring): asserts
                         an "@Reasoning : ... @End Reasoning" block produces an
                         AST_AI_ANNOTATION node carrying the right kind, name,
                         and captured content; and that an UNTERMINATED block
                         (no "@End") is a parse error (returns 0 and records a
                         diagnostic).
  Macro AST algorithms -> MacroExpansion.macro_deep_clone (structural copy is
                         independent of the original under mutation),
                         macro_substitute_identifier (parameter reference is
                         replaced by the argument subtree), and
                         macro_rename_identifier (alpha-rename leaves no
                         occurrence of the captured name).

The annotation parser and the macro algorithms link against the deferred
parser-core objects (parser/expression_parsers/statement_parsers, staged in
deferred_parsing/), so this probe is the dependency-isolated faithful check
for the #494 batch.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/annotation_parser.runa" as AnnotationParser
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/macro_expansion.runa" as MacroExpansion
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/ast.runa" as AST
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/syntax_transformer.runa" as SyntaxTransformer
Import "compiler/frontend/lexical/token_stream.runa" as TokenStream
Import "compiler/frontend/parsing/parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: Canonical token-type constants (single source of truth is the lexical
Note: subsystem; mirrored here for the probe).
Constant TOKEN_EOF as Integer is 0
Constant TOKEN_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 200
Constant TOKEN_COLON as Integer is 206
Constant TOKEN_AT as Integer is 653

Note: AST node-type discriminants (from ast.runa).
Constant AST_AI_ANNOTATION as Integer is 7000
Constant AST_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 1001
Constant AST_LITERAL as Integer is 1000
Constant AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION as Integer is 1002

Note: Annotation kind constant (from annotation_parser.runa).
Constant ANNOTATION_REASONING as Integer is 1

Process called "build_token" takes token_type as Integer, text as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Build a single lexical Token of the given type carrying the given value
    string at line 1, column 1, length 1. Uses the canonical lexical token
    constructor so the layout matches what the parser's accessors read.
    :End Note
    Return proc create_token from SyntaxTransformer with token_type, text, 1, 1, 1
End Process

Process called "build_stream" takes token_array as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Build a minimal TokenStream over a Token-pointer array using the canonical
    layout (tokens@0, count@8, position@16, eof@40, filters@48/56). This
    bypasses create_token_stream so the dependency-isolated probe does not pull
    the (currently-unbuildable) internal_collections/hash_utils chain that the
    full stream constructor's backtracking ArrayList requires. The stream
    navigation primitives (stream_peek/consume/current) read only these
    offsets, so a manually-built stream drives them identically.
    :End Note
    Let stream be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 0, token_array
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 8, count
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with stream, 56, 0
    Return stream
End Process

Process called "build_parser" takes stream as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Build a minimal ParserState over a token stream using the canonical layout
    (arena@0, token_stream@8, current_token@16, error_count@32,
    diagnostics_engine@112). This bypasses parser_create so the probe avoids
    its hashtable/stack/list initialization (and the associated dependency
    pull) while exercising the exact accessors the annotation parser uses. The
    diagnostics engine is left null; parser_report_error tolerates that and
    still increments error_count, which is the observable the unterminated-
    block test asserts.
    :End Note
    Let parser be proc allocate from Layout with 144
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with parser, 0, arena
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with parser, 8, stream
    Let first be proc stream_current from TokenStream with stream
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with parser, 16, first
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with parser, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with parser, 112, 0
    Return parser
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "macro + annotation probe (#494)"

    Let arena be proc arena_create from Layout with 65536

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 1. Parse a well-formed "@Reasoning : ... @End Reasoning" block.
    Note: Token stream: @ Reasoning : cache hits @ End Reasoning EOF
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let at_open be proc build_token with TOKEN_AT, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "@"
    Let kw_reasoning be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Reasoning"
    Let colon be proc build_token with TOKEN_COLON, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ":"
    Let body_a be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "cache"
    Let body_b be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "hits"
    Let at_close be proc build_token with TOKEN_AT, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "@"
    Let kw_end be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "End"
    Let kw_reasoning2 be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Reasoning"
    Let eof_tok be proc build_token with TOKEN_EOF, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ""

    Note: Lay out a 9-slot array of Token pointers.
    Let token_array be proc allocate from Layout with 72
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 0, at_open
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 8, kw_reasoning
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 16, colon
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 24, body_a
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 32, body_b
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 40, at_close
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 48, kw_end
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 56, kw_reasoning2
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with token_array, 64, eof_tok

    Let stream be proc build_stream with token_array, 9
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "token stream built", stream

    Let parser be proc build_parser with stream, arena
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser created over stream", parser

    Note: Detection: parser is positioned at a Reasoning annotation opener.
    Let detected_kind be proc parser_at_annotation_block from AnnotationParser with parser
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "annotation opener detected as Reasoning", detected_kind, ANNOTATION_REASONING

    Let anno be proc parse_annotation_block from AnnotationParser with parser
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "annotation block parsed", anno

    Let anno_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with anno
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "annotation node type is AST_AI_ANNOTATION", anno_type, AST_AI_ANNOTATION

    Let anno_kind be proc annotation_node_get_kind from AnnotationParser with anno
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "annotation kind is Reasoning", anno_kind, ANNOTATION_REASONING

    Let anno_name be proc annotation_node_get_name from AnnotationParser with anno
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "annotation name is Reasoning", anno_name, "Reasoning"

    Let anno_content be proc annotation_node_get_content from AnnotationParser with anno
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "annotation content captured", anno_content
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "annotation content text", anno_content, "cache hits"

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 2. Unterminated annotation block is a parse error.
    Note: Token stream: @ Reasoning : cache EOF  (no @End closer)
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let u_at be proc build_token with TOKEN_AT, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "@"
    Let u_kw be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Reasoning"
    Let u_colon be proc build_token with TOKEN_COLON, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ":"
    Let u_body be proc build_token with TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "cache"
    Let u_eof be proc build_token with TOKEN_EOF, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with ""

    Let u_array be proc allocate from Layout with 40
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with u_array, 0, u_at
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with u_array, 8, u_kw
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with u_array, 16, u_colon
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with u_array, 24, u_body
    proc memory_set_qword from Layout with u_array, 32, u_eof

    Let u_stream be proc build_stream with u_array, 5
    Let u_parser be proc build_parser with u_stream, arena

    Let errors_before be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with u_parser, 32
    Let u_result be proc parse_annotation_block from AnnotationParser with u_parser
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "unterminated annotation block returns 0", u_result, 0

    Let errors_after be proc memory_get_qword from Layout with u_parser, 32
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "unterminated block records a diagnostic", errors_after, errors_before

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 3. macro_deep_clone produces an independent subtree.
    Note: Build a binary-expression subtree (root + 2 identifier children),
    Note: clone it, mutate the clone, and assert the original is untouched.
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let orig_root be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION, 1, 1
    Let orig_left be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 1, 1
    Let orig_right be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 1, 5
    Let name_left be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "a"
    Let name_right be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "b"
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with orig_left, name_left, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with orig_right, name_right, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with orig_root, orig_left
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with orig_root, orig_right

    Let clone_root be proc macro_deep_clone from MacroExpansion with orig_root
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "deep clone built", clone_root

    Note: Clone is a distinct node from the original.
    proc assert_not_equal from TestUtils with results, "clone root is a distinct node", clone_root, orig_root

    Let clone_child_count be proc ast_node_get_child_count from AST with clone_root
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "clone preserves child count", clone_child_count, 2

    Let clone_left be proc ast_node_get_child from AST with clone_root, 0
    proc assert_not_equal from TestUtils with results, "clone child is a distinct node", clone_left, orig_left

    Let clone_left_name be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with clone_left
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "clone child copies value", clone_left_name, "a"

    Note: Mutate the clone's left child; the original's left child is unchanged.
    Let mutated_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "MUTATED"
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with clone_left, mutated_name, AST_IDENTIFIER

    Let orig_left_name_after be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with orig_left
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "original unchanged after clone mutation", orig_left_name_after, "a"

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 4. macro_substitute_identifier replaces a parameter reference.
    Note: Body: ( x b ) where x is the parameter. Substitute x -> literal node
    Note: valued "ARG"; assert the first child is now that argument value.
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let sub_root be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION, 2, 1
    Let sub_param_ref be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 2, 1
    Let sub_other be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 2, 5
    Let param_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "x"
    Let other_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "b"
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with sub_param_ref, param_name, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with sub_other, other_name, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with sub_root, sub_param_ref
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with sub_root, sub_other

    Let argument be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_LITERAL, 2, 1
    Let arg_value be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "ARG"
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with argument, arg_value, AST_LITERAL

    Let sub_ok be proc macro_substitute_identifier from MacroExpansion with sub_root, param_name, argument
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "substitute returns success", sub_ok, 1

    Let sub_first be proc ast_node_get_child from AST with sub_root, 0
    Let sub_first_type be proc ast_node_get_type from AST with sub_first
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "substituted slot is the argument node type", sub_first_type, AST_LITERAL

    Let sub_first_value be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with sub_first
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "substituted slot carries argument value", sub_first_value, "ARG"

    Note: The non-matching child is untouched.
    Let sub_second be proc ast_node_get_child from AST with sub_root, 1
    Let sub_second_value be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with sub_second
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "non-matching child untouched", sub_second_value, "b"

    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Note: 5. macro_rename_identifier alpha-renames with no leftover capture.
    Note: Body: ( t t ) both named "t". Rename t -> t_unique; assert both
    Note: occurrences are renamed and none still reads "t".
    Note: -------------------------------------------------------------------
    Let ren_root be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_BINARY_EXPRESSION, 3, 1
    Let ren_a be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 3, 1
    Let ren_b be proc create_ast_node from AST with AST_IDENTIFIER, 3, 5
    Let old_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "t"
    Let old_name2 be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "t"
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with ren_a, old_name, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_set_value from AST with ren_b, old_name2, AST_IDENTIFIER
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with ren_root, ren_a
    proc ast_node_add_child from AST with ren_root, ren_b

    Let new_name be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "t_unique"
    Let match_old be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "t"
    Let ren_ok be proc macro_rename_identifier from MacroExpansion with ren_root, match_old, new_name
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "rename returns success", ren_ok, 1

    Let ren_a_after be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with ren_a
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "first occurrence renamed", ren_a_after, "t_unique"

    Let ren_b_after be proc ast_node_get_value from AST with ren_b
    proc assert_string_equal from TestUtils with results, "second occurrence renamed (no capture left)", ren_b_after, "t_unique"

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results

    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    Return failed
End Process
